newArtists.name: Grace VanderWaal
newArtists.content: Grace Avery VanderWaal (born January 15, 2004) is an American singer-songwriter from Suffern, NY. At age 12, she won the 11th season of the NBC competition show America's Got Talent, singing her original songs and usually accompanying herself on the ukulele. Known for her distinctive vocals, she launched her first full-length album.

newArtists.name: Courtney Hadwin
newArtists.content: Courtney Ann Hadwin (born 6 July 2004) is a British singer-songwriter, best known for competing on the ITV's The Voice Kids UK 2017 and the thirteenth season of the NBC competition show America's Got Talent. In December 2018, Hadwin signed a record deal with Syco Entertainment and Arista Records.[21] Her first album is expected in 2019. She has been described as an exceptional talent with a voice and spirit well beyond her years.

newArtists.name: Juice WRLD
newArtists.content: Jarad Higgins, known professionally as Juice WRLD, is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter from Calumet Park, Illinois. He is primarily known for his breakout hits, All Girls Are the Same and Lucid Dreams. His music has been described as emo-leaning and genre-bending. Jared Higgins was born on December 2, 1998 in Chicago and grew up in Calumet Park, one of its suburbs. He later moved to Homewood, Illinois and attended Homewood-Flossmoor High School.

newArtists.name: Ella Mai
newArtists.content: Ella Mai Howell (born November 3, 1994) is an English singer and songwriter. She signed to DJ Mustard's label 10 Summers Records in 2014. Her EP's include Time, Change, and Ready. Her self-titled debut studio album was released in October 2018 and featured the singles Boo'd Up and Trip, which were released on February 20, 2018 and August 3, 2018, respectively.
